credit.credit-words: But God from infant tongues On earth receiveth praise; We then our cheerful songs In sweet accord will raise: Alleluia! We too will sing Alleluia! We too will sing To God our King Alleluia!
O, may Thy holy Word Spread all the world around! And all with one accord Uplift the joyful sound: Alleluia! All then shall sing Alleluia! All then shall sing To God their King Alleluia!

direction-type.words: And teach us in our youth
To know Thee as Thou art.
